.TH DOTFILES\-MANAGER 1 "2026-04-09" "1.4.1" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
dotfiles\-manager \- dmenu dotfiles launcher into a tmux session or neovim
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY dotfiles\-manager
.OP subcommand
.OP args
.YS
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dotfiles\-manager
is a dmenu\-driven launcher for managing dotfiles subdirectories.
It picks a configured subdir via dmenu and opens it either in a single
shared tmux session
.RB ( dots )
or in neovim with a telescope fuzzy finder, depending on the configured mode.
.PP
The mode can be set globally in the settings file and overridden per\-entry
inline in the repos file.
When a tmux session named
.B dots
already exists, the tool attaches to it rather than creating a new one.
.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
When called with no arguments,
.B dotfiles\-manager
opens a dmenu picker and launches the selected entry.
.TP
.B list
List all configured entries with their resolved mode, sync status, and target
path. Also shows the active dotfiles directory and whether a
.B dots
tmux session is running.
.TP
.B kill
Kill the
.B dots
tmux session after confirmation.
.TP
.B edit
Open the repos config file in
.BR $EDITOR .
.TP
.B settings
Open the global settings file in
.BR $EDITOR .
.TP
.BI add " name " [ mode ]
Add
.I name
to the repos config.
.I mode
is optional and must be
.B vim
or
.BR tmux .
.TP
.BI remove " name"
Remove
.I name
from the repos config.
.TP
.BI mode " name " vim | tmux | clear
Set or clear the per\-entry mode override for
.I name
without manually editing the repos file.
.B clear
strips the override and falls back to the global default.
.TP
.BI cd " name"
Print the absolute path of the subdir for
.IR name .
Intended for use with a shell function:
.PP
.RS
.EX
cd "$(dotfiles\-manager cd \fIname\fP)"
.EE
.RE
.TP
.BI apply " name"
Copy
.IB dotfiles_dir / name /
to its resolved target directory, backing up the existing target first.
Up to 10 timestamped backups are kept per target; older ones are pruned.
.TP
.B apply\-all
Run
.B apply
for every entry in the repos config.
.TP
.BI map " name path"
Set a custom destination path for
.IR name ,
overriding the default of
.IR ~/.config/ name .
.TP
.B \-h\fR,\fP \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version string and exit.
.
.TP
.B rollback <name>
Roll back a configured entry to a previously backed-up version.
Presents a dmenu picker to choose which backup to restore.
.SH SESSION MODES
.B dotfiles\-manager
supports two modes for opening a dotfiles subdir.
.TP
.B tmux
Create a new tmux session named
.B dots
with its working directory set to the subdir, or attach to the existing
.B dots
session if one is already running.
This is the default mode.
.TP
.B vim
Launch neovim with
.B telescope.nvim
opened via
.BR find_files ,
rooted at the subdir.
If telescope is not installed, neovim falls back to opening the directory in
.BR netrw .
If neither
.B nvim
nor
.B vim
is found, the tool exits with an error.
.PP
Mode resolution follows this priority order (highest to lowest):
.IP 1. 4
Per\-entry override in the repos file
.RI ( "name mode=vim" ).
.IP 2. 4
Global
.B mode
key in the settings file.
.IP 3. 4
Hardcoded fallback:
.BR tmux .
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/dotfiles\-manager/repos
List of dotfiles subdirs, one per line.
Blank lines and lines starting with
.B #
are ignored.
Each entry may carry an optional inline mode override:
.PP
.RS
.EX
nvim mode=vim
dwm\-btw mode=tmux
hypr
.EE
.RE
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/dotfiles\-manager/settings
Global key\-value configuration.
Blank lines and lines starting with
.B #
are ignored.
Supported keys:
.RS
.TP
.B mode
Default session mode.
Must be
.B vim
or
.BR tmux .
Defaults to
.B tmux
if unset.
.TP
.B dotfiles_dir
Root directory that contains the dotfiles subdirs.
Tilde
.RB ( ~ )
is expanded.
Overridden by the
.B DOTFILES_DIR
environment variable.
Defaults to
.I ~/dotfiles
if unset.
.RE
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/dotfiles\-manager/mappings
Custom destination path overrides, one per line, in the format:
.PP
.RS
.EX
name = /absolute/target/path
.EE
.PP
When a mapping is set for an entry, it is used instead of the default
.IR ~/.config/ name .
.RE
.TP
.I $HOME/.local/share/dotfiles\-manager/log.txt
Operation log with timestamps.
.TP
.I $HOME/.local/share/dotfiles\-manager/backups/
Timestamped backups created before each
.B apply
operation.
At most 10 backups are kept per target; older ones are pruned automatically.
.
.SH DOTFILES DIR RESOLUTION
The root dotfiles directory is resolved in this order:
.IP 1. 4
.B $DOTFILES_DIR
environment variable.
.IP 2. 4
.B dotfiles_dir
key in the settings file.
.IP 3. 4
.I ~/dotfiles
(hardcoded fallback).
.PP
A non\-fatal warning is printed if the resolved directory does not exist.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DOTFILES_DIR
Overrides the dotfiles root directory.
Takes priority over
.B dotfiles_dir
in the settings file.
.TP
.B EDITOR
Editor used by the
.B edit
and
.B settings
subcommands.
Defaults to
.BR vi .
.TP
.B TERMINAL
Terminal emulator used when opening tmux or neovim outside an existing
terminal context.
Auto\-detected from
.BR alacritty ,
.BR kitty ,
.BR foot ,
and
.B st
(in that order) if unset.
.TP
.B DOTFILES_DMENU_NB
dmenu normal background color.
Default:
.IR #1a1b26 .
.TP
.B DOTFILES_DMENU_NF
dmenu normal foreground color.
Default:
.IR #c0caf5 .
.TP
.B DOTFILES_DMENU_SB
dmenu selected background color.
Default:
.IR #7aa2f7 .
.TP
.B DOTFILES_DMENU_SF
dmenu selected foreground color.
Default:
.IR #1a1b26 .
.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B dmenu
Required for the interactive picker.
.TP
.B tmux
Required for tmux mode and session management.
.TP
.BR nvim (1)
or
.BR vim (1)
Required for vim mode.
.TP
.BR telescope.nvim
Optional neovim plugin.
Used for fuzzy file picking in vim mode.
Falls back to netrw if not installed.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
Open the dmenu picker and launch the selected subdir:
.PP
.RS
.EX
dotfiles\-manager
.EE
.RE
.PP
Add an entry that always opens in neovim:
.PP
.RS
.EX
dotfiles\-manager add nvim vim
.EE
.RE
.PP
Switch an existing entry to vim mode:
.PP
.RS
.EX
dotfiles\-manager mode hypr vim
.EE
.RE
.PP
Apply your nvim dotfiles to their target:
.PP
.RS
.EX
dotfiles\-manager apply nvim
.EE
.RE
.PP
Use a non\-default dotfiles directory for one invocation:
.PP
.RS
.EX
DOTFILES_DIR=~/work/dots dotfiles\-manager
.EE
.RE
.PP
Jump into a subdir from your shell:
.PP
.RS
.EX
cd "$(dotfiles\-manager cd hypr)"
.EE
.RE
.
.SH BUGS
When a
.B dots
tmux session already exists, attaching always lands in that session's current
working directory rather than the newly selected subdir.
Use
.B dotfiles\-manager kill
to reset the session.
.PP
The
.B apply
subcommand does a full recursive copy and does not remove files that were
deleted from the source subdir.
Stale files must be cleaned from the target manually.
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dmenu (1),
.BR tmux (1),
.BR nvim (1),
.BR stow (8),
.BR chezmoi (1)
